arch-home
Contact: pyther@pyther.net
Website: http://pyther.net/projects/arch-home/

Description: arch-home is a webpy script that generates an Arch Linux homepage.

Features

    * News Headlines
    * Latest Packages
    * Google, Arch Forums, Wiki, and Aur Search
    * Arch Logo

Dependencies:

    * Python 2.6
    * python-feedparser 4.1 - http://www.feedparser.org/
    * webpy 3.0 - http://webpy.org/
    * feedcache 1.3.1 - http://www.doughellmann.com/projects/feedcache/
    * python-flup 1.0.1 (this is really a webpy depend)


Download:

    - Development Code (git): http://github.com/pyther/arch-home 
    - Stable Releases: http://github.com/pyther/arch-home/downloads

How to use:

    -Configure webserver to use this webpy script. (See webpy site for instructions)
    -Execute ./index.py  (Use this only for personal usage, do not publish on the web!) 


Bugs/Feature Requests:
    Please submit all bugs and feature requests here: http://github.com/pyther/arch-home/issues


Things to Know:
    *If the package name is longer than 28 characters it will be truncated. However if you hover over the package a tooltip will appear with the full name.
    *The rss feed is cached: 15 min - pkgs, 30 min - news (Can be modified in index.py)

